subSection.paragraph:
All known
Fernandezina species
are epigean taxa known from forested environments, including Caribbean (
Cala-Riquelme et al. 2018
; Martínez & Gutierrez 2021 ), Andean (
Cala-Riquelme et al. 2018
), Amazonian (
Buckup & Ott 2004
;
Piacentini et al. 2013
), restingas and Atlantic (
Castro et al. 2015
) forests. In these environments, the reported specimens were collected either with pitfall traps (e.g.,
Castro et al. 2015
;
Piacentini et al. 2013
), searching in or sifting the leaf litter (e.g.,
Cala-Riquelme et al. 2018
;
Castro et al. 2015
;
Piacentini et al. 2013
). Recently, spider samplings carried out inside and outside limestone caves in the Brazilian semiarid domain revealed the first hypogean
Fernandezina species.
Along with this cave species, a second epigean
Fernandezina species
is described in the present study, based on specimens collected in the same expedition.

